# 🟢 Problem 1: Smart Home Device

```java
abstract class SmartDevice {
    abstract void turnOn();
    abstract void turnOff();
    abstract void showStatus();
}

class Light extends SmartDevice {
    void turnOn() {
        System.out.println("Light ON (70% brightness)");
    }
    void turnOff() {
        System.out.println("Light OFF");
    }
    void showStatus() {
        System.out.println("Brightness: 70%");
    }
}

class Fan extends SmartDevice {
    void turnOn() {
        System.out.println("Fan ON (Speed 3)");
    }
    void turnOff() {
        System.out.println("Fan OFF");
    }
    void showStatus() {
        System.out.println("Speed: 3");
    }
}
```

👉 Idea: **same method, different device → different behavior (Polymorphism)**

